&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Please submit your CV in English only&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Here at AppsFlyer, it’s all about the people, each and everyone of us has our own specialty, a unique flavor that we bring to the table. We are all driven individuals whose interests are just as diverse as we are. You could say we’re #PeopleObsessed. When we say obsession, we mean we will do everything to make you feel those AF vibes; whether it’s company breakfasts, happy hours and parties, our connection to each other is always a core focus.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a well-rounded Partner Solutions Engineer to be based in our Argentina office, advising and solving implementation requirements for global partners. The ideal candidate is passionate about the mobile advertising ecosystem, and has a successful track record of providing service and support to industry players. He/she will help guide our partners to navigate AppsFlyer’s partner-facing technology, and advise on best practices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be comfortable in a fast-paced environment, thrive in developing new opportunities and working in a global company.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Provide technical consultation and support during integration implementation, integration update, troubleshooting and resolving any related issues&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Answer incoming inquiries from ad network, agency and marketing technology partners on various technical topics related to AppsFlyer’s product offering&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Solve complex technical issues through strong collaboration with R&amp;amp;D, Product and Analysts&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Work closely with AppsFlyer business and delivery teams to coordinate, prioritize and monitor integration activities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Help new partners learn AppsFlyer’s product suite and discover the full potential of their integration&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Take ownership on specific technical domains and processes to enrich the entire Partner Solutions team’s overall scope of expertise&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Provide continuous feedback through internal feedback loops to guide product direction and roadmap&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Actively leverages AI-related tools to improve daily work efficiency. Proactively identifies areas in day-to-day operations that can be automated and contributes to driving AI automation initiatives toward implementation&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;2+ years of&amp;nbsp;experience as a Technical Engineer/Customer Support Engineer/Integration Engineer in a mobile/SaaS/adtech company&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Strong written and verbal communication skills in English&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Superior analytical and problem solving skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ability to understand business cases and requirements to build out technical solutions&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ability to lead tech discussions and understanding business needs&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience with SQL and Client Server architecture&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Self-motivated learner with endless curiosity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Passion for providing best-in-class service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bonus Points:&lt;

&lt;p&gt;AppsFlyer is a global SaaS company trusted by leading brands such as Meta, TikTok, Nike, and eBay to measure, analyze, and optimize their growth. Our platform processes billions of events daily, and product design plays a crucial role in turning that complexity into clarity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a talented and experienced Product Designer to help shape the future of our B2B platform. In this role, you’ll join the Creative unit, working as part of a cross-functional squad alongside product managers, engineers, Data Scientists and analysts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Creative, we develop a platform equipped with cutting-edge AI-powered tools to tackle any creative production and optimization challenge. This empowers advertisers to maximize the performance of their marketing campaigns and achieve their business objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll take full ownership of the design process - from uncovering user needs and surfacing hidden opportunities to ideating, prototyping, and designing intuitive, visually polished solutions. You’ll also play a key role in building feedback loops that help the product evolve and deliver meaningful impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead end-to-end product design: research, ideation, flows, wireframes, visual design&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design intuitive, user-centered solutions in a data-rich B2B environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate complex workflows into accessible product experiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with product managers, engineers, analysts, and fellow designers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate design reviews, usability tests, and continuous iteration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the Design System and design culture at large scale&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;3-5 &lt;/span&gt;years of experience designing digital products end-to-end&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Background in B2B or complex systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Strong portfolio showcasing UX thinking and refined UI execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Proficiency in Figma and familiarity with design systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication and collaboration skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bonus Points&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Bachelor’s Degree in a relevant program (Visual Communications, Industrial Design, Interaction Design, HCI)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience designing data tools, analytics platforms, or marketing technologies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recommended by an AppsFlyer employee&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a global company operating from 25 offices across 19 countries, we reflect the human mosaic of the diverse and multicultural world in which we live. We ensure equal opportunities for all of our employees and promote the recruitment of diverse talents to our global teams without consideration of race, gender, culture, or sexual orientation. We value and encourage curiosity, diversity, and innovation from all our employees, customers, and partners.&lt;/p&gt;
