&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;AppsFlyer is the market leader in mobile attribution and marketing analytics, serving thousands of customers worldwide. Our data is our biggest asset, and we leverage it to help businesses thrive in the digital age.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;AppsFlyer offers a broad portfolio of data export products, including Data Locker, that thousands of customers rely on to access and operationalize their data at scale. As more customers build in-house AI and data science initiatives, their need for reliable, flexible, high-quality data export is only growing, making these products a foundational piece of their data stack.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a Product Manager to own all of AppsFlyer&#39;s data export products end-to-end. This is a hands-on role with high customer exposure: you&#39;ll work directly with enterprise clients to understand their data access needs, partner closely with internal stakeholders across the organization, and ship improvements across multiple product surfaces in parallel. If you thrive on juggling priorities, communicating clearly across audiences, and turning customer feedback into shipped products, this role is for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own all of AppsFlyer&#39;s data export products throughout their lifecycles, from discovery and definition through delivery, adoption, and iteration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner directly with enterprise customers and internal stakeholders to understand data export pain points and translate them into clear requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prioritize effectively across multiple product surfaces and competing stakeholder needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive cross-functional alignment with engineering and business teams to deliver high-quality features on time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and communicate product roadmap, trade-offs, and decisions clearly, both to internal teams and customer-facing audiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously improve usability, reliability, and documentation based on customer feedback and usage data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strengthen and expand AppsFlyer&#39;s data export products as the foundation for customers&#39; AI and advanced analytics initiatives by ensuring we deliver the right data, in the right format, at the right cadence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3-5 years of experience as a Product Manager&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in a technical field such as Computer Science or Engineering, or equivalent practical experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working on user-facing B2B products and services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent English communication skills, written and verbal, with comfort presenting to customers and internal stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing multiple concurrent workstreams with competing priorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working closely with customer-facing teams and incorporating their input into product decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with data pipelines, APIs, or SaaS data infrastructure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong execution skills with the ability to mobilize cross-functional teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Team player with a &quot;can-do&quot; approach: takes ownership, acts with urgency, operates independently&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bonus Points:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Practical knowledge of digital marketing and advertising technologies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience as a Data Analyst, Data Engineer, BI Engineer, or similar&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Big Data technologies and infrastructure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with data export, ETL, or data delivery products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
